
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gtk-builder-tool` baraye check kardane file-haye `GtkBuilder` (ke baraye tarrahi UI estefade mishan) az nazar error va eshtebahat be kar mire. In tool komak mikone ke UI dorost va bedoon moshkel kar kone. 

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `gtk-builder-tool validate FILENAME`  --> 🔍 File `FILENAME` ro az nazar doros boodan check mikone.
    🔹 `gtk-builder-tool simplify FILENAME`  --> ✨ File `FILENAME` ro sade mikone va size-esh ro kam mikone.
    🔹 `gtk-builder-tool inspect FILENAME`  --> 🕵️‍♀️ Element-haye dakhele file `FILENAME` ro neshun mide va etela'ati dar moredeshun mide.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gtk-builder-tool validate my_window.ui

    🔹 File `my_window.ui` ro check mikone ke moshkeli nadashte bashe.

    $ gtk-builder-tool simplify my_window.ui > my_window_simplified.ui

    🔹 File `my_window.ui` ro sade mikone va natije ro too `my_window_simplified.ui` zakhire mikone.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gtk-builder-tool validate my_window.ui
    my_window.ui:42:3: warning: Property “visible” is deprecated and shouldn't be used anymore.

    🔹 Age `gtk-builder-tool` warning ya error peyda kone, mesle bala neshun mide.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gtk-builder-tool` command is used to validate `GtkBuilder` files (used for UI design) for errors and inconsistencies. This tool helps ensure that the UI works correctly and without issues.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `gtk-builder-tool validate FILENAME`  --> 🔍 Checks the `FILENAME` file for validity.
    🔹 `gtk-builder-tool simplify FILENAME`  --> ✨ Simplifies the `FILENAME` file and reduces its size.
    🔹 `gtk-builder-tool inspect FILENAME`  --> 🕵️‍♂️ Inspects the elements inside the `FILENAME` file and provides information about them.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gtk-builder-tool validate my_window.ui

    🔹 Checks the `my_window.ui` file for any issues.

    $ gtk-builder-tool simplify my_window.ui > my_window_simplified.ui

    🔹 Simplifies the `my_window.ui` file and saves the result to `my_window_simplified.ui`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gtk-builder-tool validate my_window.ui
    my_window.ui:42:3: warning: Property “visible” is deprecated and shouldn't be used anymore.

    🔹 If `gtk-builder-tool` finds any warnings or errors, it will display them as shown above.
